EVP and CFO of D (NYSE:DHI), Wheat Bill W, sells 2,780 shares worth $89,970
According to D's most recent Form 4 filing with the SEC dated Mar 07 06:30 PM, company EVP and CFO, Wheat Bill W disclosed selling 2,780 shares at a cost of $32.36. At the time of this transaction (Mar 06), this trade was worth $89,970 in total. As of Mar 06, Wheat Bill W now owns 109,997 shares in total worth about $3,613,401.45. 
For the last few recent trades made by D (NYSE:DHI) EVP and CFO, Wheat Bill W, we have the following information:




SEC Form 4 filing: Feb 13: Sold 2,925 shares at the rate of $30.54 per share. Total worth of this trade was $89,331. Total number of shares owned as of Feb 13 were 93,697
SEC Form 4 filing: May 02: Sold 40,000 shares at the rate of $30.37 per share. Total worth of this trade was $1,214,652. Total number of shares owned as of May 02 were 68,014
SEC Form 4 filing: Mar 07: Sold 2,838 shares at the rate of $28.17 per share. Total worth of this trade was $79,956. Total number of shares owned as of Mar 07 were 68,014




